### What topics should I know before coming? 
Basic Linux knowledge is strongly recommended. 

### Should I install something before coming? 
Yes! 

For Windows: https://store.docker.com/editions/community/docker-ce-desktop-windows
If this doesn't work, try the following link: 
https://docs.docker.com/toolbox/toolbox_install_windows/

For Mac:
https://store.docker.com/editions/community/docker-ce-desktop-mac

For Linux: 
You can install docker through the  package manager -- thename to download is docker-ce.

PLEASE NOTE: If you can't get it done before the workshop, no worries! Either email alan@adicu.com or come in to the workshop and we'll help you out!

### Can I use a PC, a Chromebook, or a X computer? 
Yes, but MacOS or Linux is recommended!

### What will I learn? 
You'll learn how to containerize apps to run on pretty much any computer without going through dependency hell.

### Is there a way to contact any of the event organizers if I have questions not listed here? 
If you have any questions about this event please contact lesley@adicu.com

Clarifying Terms:
- Dependency: When an object uses a function of another object. 
- Containers: A container is an executable package that includes everything needed to run it, without the need to depend on objects outside of the image. 
- Docker: A software technology that provides containers to developers!